## Summary
- update RFC 0003 around policy conformance, not a general artifact audit
- add `exec-approvals.json` as the first named product artifact policy can read through explicit opt-in and redacted evidence
- document the roadmap boundary: P1 exec approvals/sandbox mode allowlists, P2 config-backed posture, P3 only low-noise static posture if justified
- add concrete `execApprovals` policy-rule and evidence-shape examples

## Policy example
```jsonc
{
  "execApprovals": {
    "requireFile": true,
    "defaults": {
      // Security modes: "deny", "allowlist", or "full".
      // This default permits only the locked-down deny posture.
      "allowSecurity": ["deny"]
    }
  },
  "scopes": {
    "restricted-shell": {
      "agentIds": ["family-agent", "groups-agent"],
      "execApprovals": {
        "agents": {
          // Selected agents may use reviewed allowlist posture, but not "full".
          "allowSecurity": ["allowlist"],
          "allowlist": {
            "expected": ["travel-hub", "calendar-cli", "/bin/date"]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Evidence shape
Policy evidence is redacted posture, not the raw artifact. It keeps stable `oc://` references and reviewable posture fields, while omitting socket path/token, command text, resolved paths, timestamps, and approval-session details.

```json
[
  {
    "kind": "defaults",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/defaults",
    "security": "full"
  },
  {
    "kind": "agent",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby",
    "agentId": "sebby",
    "security": "full"
  },
  {
    "kind": "allowlist",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby/allowlist/#0",
    "agentId": "sebby",
    "pattern": "deploy"
  }
]
```

Example finding:

```json
{
  "checkId": "policy/exec-approvals-agent-security-unapproved",
  "ocPath": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby",
  "requirement": "oc://policy.jsonc/execApprovals/agents/allowSecurity",
  "message": "exec approvals agent 'sebby' uses unapproved security mode 'full'."
}
```

## Related
- Stacked with openclaw/openclaw#90003

Draft while the OpenClaw policy implementation PR is under review.

